.TH PROTOND 1 "2026-06-06" "0.1.0" "Proton Drive"
.SH NAME
protond \- Proton Drive sync daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B protond
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B protond
is the background sync daemon for Proton Drive. It runs as a user service,
watches the local sync directory for changes, periodically synchronizes
with the remote server, and handles IPC requests from the CLI and GUI.
.SH USAGE
protond is typically started automatically by the GUI or via systemd:
.nf
  systemctl --user start protond
.fi
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.I XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Unix socket location for IPC (\fI$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/protond.sock\fR).
.TP
.I PROTON_DRIVE_DIR
Override the local sync directory (default: \fI~/Proton Drive\fR).
.TP
.I RUST_LOG
Set tracing/logging level (e.g., \fIinfo\fR, \fIdebug\fR, \fIwarn\fR).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/proton-drive/
SQLite database and state.
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/protond.sock
Unix domain socket for IPC.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGTERM, SIGINT
Graceful shutdown.
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/issues
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR proton-drive (1)
